"title": "5443: pillars",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5443",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Supports or decorations in buildings and free-standing memorial monuments. The word is also used figuratively, with reference to strength and beauty.</p>\n<h2>Pillars in the temple</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:21\">1KI 7:21</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Pillars erected as memorials</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:18-Gen28:22\">GEN 28:18–28:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:45-Gen31:53\">GEN 31:45–31:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:14-Gen35:15\">GEN 35:14–35:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:19-Gen35:20\">GEN 35:19–35:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:4\">EXO 24:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:2-Deut27:6\">DEU 27:2–27:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh4:1-Josh4:9\">JOS 4:1–4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:18\">2SA 18:18</a></p>\n<h2>The pillar of cloud and fire</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:21-Exod13:22\">EXO 13:21–13:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:9\">EXO 33:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:12\">NEH 9:12</a></p>\n<h2>The figurative use of pillars</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:18\">JER 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:6\">JOB 9:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job26:11\">JOB 26:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps75:3\">PSA 75:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:12\">PSA 144:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song5:15\">SNG 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:9\">GAL 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:12\">REV 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev10:1\">REV 10:1</a></p>\n<h2>Kings were sometimes crowned beside a pillar</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:6\">JDG 9:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:12-2Kgs11:14\">2KI 11:12–11:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:11-2Chr23:13\">2CH 23:11–23:13</a></p>\n<h2>Other notable incidents connected with pillars</h2>\n<h3>Lot's wife and the pillar of salt</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:24-Gen19:26\">GEN 19:24–19:26</a></p>\n<h3>Samson's destruction of a temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:25-Judg16:30\">JDG 16:25–16:30</a></p>",
